notes.content: Austatud sõbrad, tetvitan teid oma kartika Mina jõusin sia eile./ Ja töödan/ Aha olen tüdin, sid ei ole lust./ Ja nii tahan lõpetada seda linna elu sellel nädalal./ On teil seal reisimine ja rändan ka mina Nii palun kirjutage kuda teil läheb Kas arvate, et hakkame ühes uut kohta otsima, siis ehk tulen aga ehk muidu lähen üksi, paha pole, lahedam ka./ Külje peal—/Lihtsalt oma mõtted ja vastake kohe, kui võite. /Teavitades teid kõigi

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: Dear friends, sending you greetings with my card./ I arrived here yesterday, I am working, but I am fed up, it is not enjoyable here./ And so I want to finish the city life this week./ Do you plan to travel and I will journey as well./So please write, how are you all doing/ Do you think we will look for a new place together, then I will come or should I go alone, it’s not bad, maybe will be better./ These are just my thoughts. Please reply as soon as you are able to. I will wait for your reply.

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: Handwritten text on recto and verso in Hungarian.

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: (The handwriting lacks punctuation, capitalized sentence-starting and contains a lot of improper and dialect-sounding spelling, likely written by someone with limited educated.)

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: Translation, recto, on letter portion of image: I'm sending [this] to you, Dear Józska [=Hungarian endearing diminutive of Joseph]

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: I wish you a Mary Christmas and New Year

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: God be with you ['poc'(?) is nonsense, perhaps stands for "peck"/"kiss"] P.

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: Beloved Dear good cousin [=male, older]/ Jozsi [=Hungarian diminutive of Joseph] with these few lines, I am informing that I

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: am well, which in turn/ I hope also to You [=formal "per Vu"(*)]. Write, how/ is it there. Really, it has been so long since [You] even/ wrote to me. Say, are you perhaps angry/ at me 'valamiént' forgive me/ that I too have not written so long, but since/ the situation is so difficult that it is not/ even describable in this warring world/ Write, Dear Józska, a few lines, I really/ will enjoy them, if a few lines/ I can read. Now I am

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: in Pest. Back home already more than a/ year I haven't been, since in the Fall/ we went to Italy, and have returned/ in May, and now I am here constantly./ When you receive my lines, write how is it there

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: and I too will write more, later/ God be with you. Countless greetings, and kiss you as your cousin [=female, younger]/ truly, Paula. 'Banesza'/'Bancsza' [?]

notes.label: Description (Brief)
notes.content: (*) Hungarian routinely uses three forms of address: a close/familiar "per Tu," a formal/respectful "per Vu" and the high-respect "Thou"
